2026-03-31T18:47:30.385Z JOY-00B6 comment.added "Root cause: sequential ID generation is not collision-safe in distributed scenarios. Two machines running joy add without sync get the same next ID. Solution: ADR-027 -- append 2 hex digits from title hash to the sequential counter. New format: JOY-0100-5C. Old IDs stay unchanged, no migration needed. Short-form input (JOY-0100) accepted when unambiguous." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-31T19:05:38.242Z JOY-00B7-6F item.created "Test collision safe ID" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-31T19:06:23.147Z JOY-00B7-6F item.deleted "Test collision safe ID" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-31T19:06:39.016Z JOY-00B6 comment.added "[x] ADR-027 implemented. New ID format: ACRONYM-XXXX-YY (sequential + title hash). Old IDs unchanged. Short-form lookup accepted when unambiguous. commit-msg hook accepts both formats. Milestones also updated. 233 tests passing, clippy clean." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
